General Accountabilities
Are you a quality conscious individual with a strong work ethic and safety mindset? If so, we have an opportunity for you. Kinectrics is seeking Full Time Temporary Laundry Line Workers to assist with the operation of an industrial laundry facility. This position is a key role for the Kinectrics Laundry Plant, with the important task of ensuring the safe and efficient operation of the laundry process lines in a fast-paced manufacturing environment. General Accountabilities include:
Operations
Responsibilities include but are not limited to operating heavy industrial equipment, systems, and components, including but not limited to washers, dryers, conveyor systems and folding machines;
Involvement in shipping and receiving of customer laundry, including verifying customer quantities;
Sorting and classifying soiled laundry in appropriate silos/carts in accordance with the type of item and contamination level;
Logging items by RFID tag and sorting for processing in accordance with procedures;
Using a proprietary software to save records of operations;
Performing manual work as needed to run the process lines, including but not limited to:
loading and unloading customer laundry into and out of machines;
hanging plastic suits onto drying racks;
moving carts/silos around the facility;
manual folding and packing of some articles upon shipping;
Loading customer laundry in batches per the operations schedule and optimized wash cycles;
Regulating machine processes i.e. turning them on/off, turning levels and valves to control the volume of additives, specific cycles and temperature;
Ensuring all computer-controlled systems are functioning correctly and no lag times/delays exist in the automated processes;
Inspecting articles for wear, tear, and colour and then mending/repairing accordingly;
Performing oversight of process lines and aiding other line workers where needed.
Safety & Procedures
Performing all duties in a safe manner and in compliance with Kinectrics policies and procedures;
Complying with quality procedures set in accordance with ISO9001;
Following all Kinectrics Technical Work Instructions related to operation of the laundry equipment;
Actively cooperating in pre-job brief discussions and identification of any hazards;
Following radiation safety standards and protocols and being familiar with the use of standard radiation protection equipment, such as personnel portal monitors, bulk monitors, small article monitors, etc.;
Involvement in scanning and monitoring of laundry items;
Understanding the unit operations for each process line and zoning divisions in the facility;
Providing support to the Radiation Protection Supervisor or RP technicians where necessary.
Maintenance & Improvements
Identifying any bottlenecks in the process lines;
Working in conjunction with plant personnel to modify and improve the processing and packaging of laundry items;
Providing support to the facilities manager and laundry supervisor where needed, including:
Informing the facilities manager of maintenance needs, such as identifying and reporting any equipment issues while operating the process lines;
Following contingency plans where necessary;
Alerting the managers when machine filters need to be changed or equipment needs repair;
Assisting in the setup, takedown or relocation of production equipment;
Maintaining inventory and communicating needs to the laundry supervisor;
Participating in other continuous improvement or process improvement initiatives;
Other general duties as required, including housekeeping, janitorial and responding to emergency alarms.
Selection Criteria
Essential Competencies:
Must have a background working in a fast-paced manufacturing environment
Ability to work under pressure, while remaining a positive team player
Must be able to organize and prioritize assigned work and to coordinate multiple activities efficiently
Team player, proactive, and quick learner
Demonstrated contributions to a strong safety-first and positive atmosphere
Strong customer orientation and commitment to Kinectrics and Business Unit goals
Ability to gain Security Clearance at a Nuclear Power Plant
Essential Knowledge, Experience and Qualifications:
High school diploma/GED
Verbal and written fluency in English
Strong verbal and written communication skills
Ability to work alone and in a team environment
Must have a strong attention to detail and to quality assurance requirements
Basic Microsoft Office computer literacy skills
Diligent in following conventional procedures
Quick learner:
Ability to follow established laundry procedures
Capable of learning how to use unique software
Desire to work efficiently
Flexible in rotating between process lines
Must be physically capable of performing the duties assigned:
Stamina needed to perform manual labor in an industrial setting, including lifting and carrying heavy objects,
dexterous, good eye-hand coordination
Ability to stand for duration of shift
An understanding of the Occupational Health & Safety Act and safety best practices, operates with a safety conscious attitude
Experience in commercial laundry would be considered an asset
Knowledge of Radiological Safety would be considered an asset
Experience in applying event-free Human Performance fundamentals would be considered an asset (understanding stop when unsure, effective (3-way) communication, procedure use and adherence, self check with verbalization)
